{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TPmiu8PdurE3kyqX4RqYMm","type":"tool_result","content":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e\n├── devnet\n│   ├── fixtures.ts\n│   ├── helpers\n│   │   ├── env.ts\n│   │   └── vrf-polling.ts\n│   ├── lifecycle.spec.ts\n│   └── smoke.spec.ts\n├── fixtures.ts\n├── local\n│   ├── 00-smoke.spec.ts\n│   ├── 01-error-flow.spec.ts\n│   ├── 02-cancel-flow.spec.ts\n│   ├── 03-lifecycle.spec.ts\n│   ├── fixtures.ts\n│   └── helpers\n│       ├── localnet-setup.ts\n│       ├── on-chain.ts\n│       ├── page-objects.ts\n│       └── wallets.ts\n├── real\n│   └── startup.spec.ts\n├── __snapshots__\n│   └── visual\n│       ├── routes.spec.ts\n│       └── states.spec.ts\n└── visual\n    ├── routes.spec.ts\n    └── states.spec.ts\n\n11 directories, 18 files","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TZpHg3AKpmaPdxmtoZJEKs","session_id":"3430a832-47ac-41dd-bbc6-e4b8a98508e0","uuid":"4073b7c7-39f3-4808-a9c3-bfeca64bb716"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TZpHg3AKpmaPdxmtoZJEKs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the E2E test structure. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## E2E Test Structure Exploration - Complete Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the rng-utopia E2E test infrastructure. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\nsources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/\n├── fixtures.ts                           (base Playwright fixture - visual regression)\n├── local/                                (local validator E2E tests)\n│   ├── 00-smoke.spec.ts\n│   ├── 01-error-flow.spec.ts\n│   ├── 02-cancel-flow.spec.ts\n│   ├── 03-lifecycle.spec.ts\n│   ├── fixtures.ts                       (dual-player fixture with keypair injection)\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── wallets.ts                    (deterministic keypairs PLAYER_A/B)\n│       ├── localnet-setup.ts             (program config init)\n│       ├── on-chain.ts                   (PDA helpers, assertions)\n│       └── page-objects.ts               (UI selectors, action helpers)\n├── devnet/                               (devnet E2E tests with real VRF)\n│   ├── fixtures.ts                       (same dual-player pattern)\n│   ├── smoke.spec.ts\n│   ├── lifecycle.spec.ts\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── env.ts                        (env var validation)\n│       └── vrf-polling.ts                (robust VRF fulfillment polling)\n├── real/\n│   └── startup.spec.ts\n├── visual/                               (visual regression tests)\n│   ├── routes.spec.ts\n│   └── states.spec.ts\n└── __snapshots__/                        (PNG baselines for visual tests)\n```\n\n### 2. What Exists\n\n#### **Local E2E Tests** (`local/`)\n- **00-smoke.spec.ts**: Minimal test - app loads, wallet icon visible, no console errors\n- **01-error-flow.spec.ts**: Three tests running serially\n  - Insufficient balance error on match creation\n  - Join unavailable (cancelled) match error\n  - Settle already-claimed match error\n- **02-cancel-flow.spec.ts**: Single test - create → cancel → verify refund → recreate\n- **03-lifecycle.spec.ts**: Full game cycle - create → join → real VRF resolve (pre-mocked) → claim → verify profiles\n- **Dual-player fixtures**: Two isolated browser contexts (`playerAPage`, `playerBPage`) with deterministic keypairs injected\n\n#### **Devnet E2E Tests** (`devnet/`)\n- **smoke.spec.ts**: Three smoke tests\n  1. Verify devnet deployments (RPC health, programs deployed, VRF initialized)\n  2. App loads against devnet\n  3. Wallet connects with test keypair\n- **lifecycle.spec.ts**: Full devnet lifecycle with real VRF fulfillment\n  - Dual strategy: on-chain polling (exponential backoff) + UI wait in parallel\n  - Real Orao VRF callback triggers phase transition (locked → resolved)\n  - Handles non-deterministic outcome (either player can win)\n  - Comprehensive logging for diagnostics\n\n#### **Visual Regression Tests** (`visual/`)\n- **routes.spec.ts**: 12 route baseline snapshots (home, coinflip, crash, profile, 404, etc.)\n- **states.spec.ts**: Connected/disconnected states for home and coinflip pages\n- Uses deterministic `stablePage` fixture that:\n  - Seeds Math.random() with seed 42 (Mulberry32 PRNG)\n  - Freezes Date.now() to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n  - Disables all CSS/SVG animations\n  - Waits for fonts.ready and network idle\n  - Detects console errors and fails test if any found\n\n#### **Real Wallet Tests** (`real/`)\n- **startup.spec.ts**: Placeholder test file (minimal content)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Coinflip E2E Test Pattern (Local)\n\nThe **local coinflip tests follow a clear progression**:\n\n**Test Flow (01-error-flow.spec.ts → 02-cancel-flow.spec.ts → 03-lifecycle.spec.ts):**\n\n```\nTest 1: Insufficient Balance\n├─ Fund Player A with 0.001 SOL (below iron tier requirement of 0.005)\n├─ Navigate to coinflip → select iron tier + heads side\n├─ Click \"Create Game\" → error toast appears\n└─ Verify no match created on-chain (PDA closed)\n\nTest 2: Cancel Flow\n├─ Fund Player A with 10 SOL\n├─ Create match → verify balance decreases\n├─ Cancel match → lobby clears, refund received\n├─ Verify match PDA closed\n└─ Recreate immediately → new match with different side\n\nTest 3: Full Lifecycle (Dual-player)\n├─ Player A creates match (iron, heads)\n├─ Player B sees match in lobby → joins\n├─ Both wait for VRF (pre-fulfilled: HEADS → A wins)\n├─ A claims payout (match PDA closes)\n└─ Verify on-chain: treasury fee, player profiles (games/wins/wagered/won)\n```\n\n**Key Selectors & Actions** (`page-objects.ts`):\n- Tier selector: `.rng-tier-btn:has(.rng-tier-gem--{tier})`\n- Side buttons: `.coinflip-side-btn--{heads|tails}`\n- Match cards: `.coinflip-match-card` (own, claimable, joinable)\n- Active match states: `.coinflip-active-match__{waiting|playing}`\n- Results: `.coinflip-active-match__title--{won|lost}`\n- Error toasts: `.coinflip-error-toast`\n\n---\n\n### 4. localnet-bootstrap.sh Deep Dive\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n\n**What it does:**\n\n1. **Preflight checks**: Ensures `.so` files, keypairs exist\n2. **Kills old validator**: Checks `.localnet.pid`, kills on port 8899 if stray\n3. **Cleans ledger**: Removes `.localnet-ledger/` for fresh state\n4. **Starts validator** with:\n   - Two programs preloaded at genesis:\n     - Coinflip program (`BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`)\n     - Platform program (`85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA`)\n   - Three Orao mock accounts pre-loaded (deterministic for tests):\n     - `5ER1oENnV4srxYdAynUfRzWeQCPQaqMiAp4VqyMbSqnK` (orao-network-state)\n     - `S4ne8ejGPUwNMNsE8L7gtjbTaBLBfVGdWNH6VQrL58a` (orao-random-player-a)\n     - `Ecs89dz8NsNoSxyUtp54G2HPbmvJr8qZnxnWUqiLT92r` (orao-treasury)\n5. **Waits for RPC**: Polls `getHealth` at `http://127.0.0.1:8899` up to 30s\n6. **Writes PID**: Saves to `.localnet.pid` for teardown\n\n**Important notes:**\n- Solana 3.x requires `io_uring`; Docker needs `--security-opt=seccomp=unconfined`\n- Script doesn't fail on io_uring check — lets validator fail naturally\n- All mock accounts in `scripts/localnet-accounts/` (JSON format for pre-initialization)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Playwright Configuration\n\n**Four configs in `apps/platform/`:**\n\n| Config | Port | Env Mode | Purpose |\n|--------|------|----------|---------|\n| `playwright.config.ts` | 3000 | MOCK | Visual regression tests (`visual/**`) |\n| `playwright.local.config.ts` | 3002 | TEST_WALLET=true, localnet RPC | Local E2E (`local/**`) |\n| `playwright.devnet.config.ts` | 3003 | TEST_WALLET=true, devnet RPC | Devnet E2E (`devnet/**`) |\n| `playwright.real.config.ts` | 3001 | Real wallet, devnet RPC | Real mode tests (`real/**`) |\n\n**Common Settings:**\n- Workers: 1 (serial execution for E2E)\n- Timeout: 60s–120s (120s for devnet due to VRF latency)\n- Trace: `retain-on-failure` for E2E, `off` for visual\n- Screenshot: off (unless visual tests use `toHaveScreenshot`)\n\n**Test-specific env vars in webServer:**\n```typescript\n// Local\nVITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"\nVITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\"\nVITE_RPC_URL: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK: \"localnet\"\n\n// Devnet\nVITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"\nVITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\"\n// VITE_RPC_URL inherited from process env (validated in devnet/helpers/env.ts)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Package.json E2E Scripts\n\n```json\n{\n  \"test:visual\": \"playwright test\",\n  \"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\",\n  \"test:real\": \"playwright test --config playwright.real.config.ts\",\n  \"test:e2e:local\": \"playwright test --config playwright.local.config.ts\",\n  \"test:e2e\": \"bash scripts/run-e2e-local.sh\",\n  \"test:e2e:devnet\": \"bash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh\"\n}\n```\n\n**Three execution modes:**\n1. **Direct Playwright**: `npm run test:e2e:local` (assumes validator already running)\n2. **Full pipeline (local)**: `npm run test:e2e` (bootstrap → test → teardown)\n3. **Devnet**: `npm run test:e2e:devnet` (no bootstrap; requires env vars)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Test Utilities & Helpers\n\n#### **wallets.ts** (Deterministic)\n```typescript\nPLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(0xaa * 32 bytes)\nPLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(0xbb * 32 bytes)\nLOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\n\nfundWallet(connection, to, solAmount = 10)\nfundTestWallets(rpcUrl, solAmount) → returns both keypairs + connection\n```\n\n#### **localnet-setup.ts** (Initialization)\n```typescript\nADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(0xdd * 32 bytes)\nTREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(0xcc * 32 bytes)\n\ninitializeLocalnet()\n  └─ Funds admin & treasury (2 SOL each)\n  └─ Initializes coinflip config PDA\n  └─ Initializes platform config PDA\n  └─ Idempotent (checks if already exists)\n\nensurePlayerProfiles()\n  └─ Creates player profile PDAs for test wallets\n  └─ Separated from initializeLocalnet() to preserve test balances\n```\n\n#### **on-chain.ts** (RPC Helpers)\n```typescript\n// PDA derivation\ngetMatchPda(creator) → [PublicKey, bump]\ngetPlayerProfilePda(wallet) → [PublicKey, bump]\n\n// Fetching\nfetchMatch(connection, pda) → MatchAccount | null\nfetchPlayerProfile(connection, pda) → PlayerProfileAccount | null\n\n// Assertions\nassertMatchCreated(connection, creator, tier, side)\nassertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)\nassertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)\nassertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)\nassertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)\n\n// Snapshots\nsnapshotBalance(connection, address)\nsnapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)\n\n// Fee calculation\ncalculateExpectedFee(entryAmount)\n  └─ Returns { pool, fee: floor(pool * 300 bps / 10000), payout }\n```\n\n#### **page-objects.ts** (UI Actions)\n```typescript\n// Navigation\nnavigateToCoinflip(page)\n\n// Creation flow\nselectTier(page, tier: \"iron\" | \"bronze\" | ... | \"diamond\")\nselectSide(page, side: \"heads\" | \"tails\")\ncreateMatch(page, tier, side)\n\n// Joining\njoinMatch(page, matchIndex = 0)\nwaitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout)\n\n// Settlement\nclaimOrSettle(page)      // Click claim/settle button\nbackToLobby(page)        // Return after claim\n\n// Waits & assertions\nwaitForResult(page, timeout) → \"won\" | \"lost\"\nwaitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)\nassertErrorToast(page, messageSubstring, timeout)\nassertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout)\n\n// Diagnostics\ntrackConsoleErrors(page) → { errors, assertClean() }\ngetSolBalance(page, walletAddress) → number\nwaitForText(page, text, timeout)\n```\n\n#### **env.ts** (Devnet Validation)\n```typescript\nvalidateDevnetEnv() → DevnetConfig\n  └─ Validates VITE_RPC_URL, VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  └─ Throws with consolidated errors if any missing/invalid\n\nverifyDevnetDeployments(config)\n  └─ RPC health check\n  └─ Programs deployed & executable\n  └─ Orao VRF network state PDA exists\n```\n\n#### **vrf-polling.ts** (Devnet VRF Detection)\n```typescript\npollVrfFulfillment(connection, creator, timeoutMs)\n  └─ Polls match PDA phase: locked → resolved\n  └─ Exponential backoff: start 2s, max 10s\n  └─ Logs timing budget at each attempt\n  └─ Returns { match, matchPda, phase, elapsedMs, attempts }\n  └─ Throws VrfTimeoutError with signatures on failure\n\ncollectMatchSignatures(connection, matchPda, limit = 10)\nlogRecentSignatures(connection, address, label, limit = 5)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Test Fixture Architecture\n\n#### **Base Fixture** (`fixtures.ts` - root)\n```typescript\nstablePage: Page\n  ├─ Seeds Math.random (Mulberry32, seed 42)\n  ├─ Seeds crypto.getRandomValues\n  ├─ Freezes Date.now to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n  ├─ Injects CSS disabling animations/transitions\n  ├─ Pauses SVG SMIL animations\n  ├─ Waits for fonts.ready + network idle after every navigation\n  └─ Collects console errors, fails test if any found\n```\n\n#### **Local Fixture** (`local/fixtures.ts`)\n```typescript\nDualPlayerFixtures {\n  playerAContext, playerAPage, playerAKeypair\n  playerBContext, playerBPage, playerBKeypair\n  connection: Connection(LOCAL_RPC_URL)\n}\n```\nEach context injects seed via `addInitScript`, allowing `TestWalletProvider` to reconstruct keypair.\n\n#### **Devnet Fixture** (`devnet/fixtures.ts`)\n```typescript\nDevnetDualPlayerFixtures {\n  devnetConfig: DevnetConfig (validates env)\n  playerAContext, playerAPage, playerAKeypair\n  playerBContext, playerBPage, playerBKeypair\n  connection: Connection(devnetConfig.rpcUrl)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Execution Flow Diagram\n\n```\nrun-e2e-local.sh\n├─ localnet-bootstrap.sh\n│  ├─ Kill old validator\n│  ├─ Clean ledger\n│  ├─ Start solana-test-validator with programs + mock accounts\n│  └─ Wait for RPC ready\n├─ playwright test --config playwright.local.config.ts\n│  ├─ Start Vite dev server (port 3002, TEST_WALLET=true)\n│  ├─ Run e2e/local/**/*.spec.ts\n│  │  ├─ beforeAll: fundTestWallets(), initializeLocalnet(), ensurePlayerProfiles()\n│  │  ├─ Each test gets playerAPage, playerBPage fixtures\n│  │  └─ Serial execution (fullyParallel: false)\n│  └─ Report results\n└─ localnet-teardown.sh\n   ├─ Kill validator by PID\n   ├─ Kill stray on port 8899\n   ├─ Remove .localnet-ledger\n   └─ Remove .localnet-validator.log (unless --keep-logs)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. Key Contract Points for New Tests\n\n**For Local Coinflip E2E (pattern to follow):**\n1. Use `test.describe.configure({ mode: \"serial\" })` for multi-test suites\n2. Fund test wallets in `beforeAll` with amounts matching test goals\n3. Call `initializeLocalnet()` before any on-chain assertions\n4. Derive PDAs using `getMatchPda()`, `getPlayerProfilePda()`\n5. Use page-objects for all UI interactions\n6. Track console errors with `po.trackConsoleErrors()`\n7. Assert on-chain state with `assert*()` helpers from `on-chain.ts`\n8. Snapshot balances & profiles before transactions, assert deltas after\n\n**For Devnet Tests:**\n1. Validate env in fixture setup (`devnetConfig` fixture)\n2. Fund wallets in `beforeAll` with airdrop (retries twice on failure)\n3. Use `pollVrfFulfillment()` for VRF wait (logs timing budget)\n4. Run UI wait in parallel with on-chain poll (whichever resolves first)\n5. Handle non-deterministic outcomes (either player can win on real VRF)\n6. Log transaction signatures for post-failure diagnostics\n\n---\n\n### 11. Summary of Files\n\n**Total Files:**\n- **Test specs**: 8 files (4 local, 2 devnet, 1 real, 1 visual baseline)\n- **Helpers**: 8 files (wallets, localnet-setup, on-chain, page-objects, env, vrf-polling, fixtures x2)\n- **Config**: 4 playwright configs + 3 shell scripts\n- **Snapshots**: Visual regression baselines in `__snapshots__/`\n\n**Key Absolute Paths:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-teardown.sh`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts`\n\nThis structure provides a robust, well-organized E2E test suite with clear separation between local deterministic tests (mock VRF), devnet real tests (real Orao VRF), and visual regression baselines."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a582ec9 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 79257\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 120028</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3430a832-47ac-41dd-bbc6-e4b8a98508e0","uuid":"378b1c61-539a-45fa-a4ac-321fa5d185c5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the E2E test structure in the rng-utopia codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. What exists in `sources/rng-utopia/e2e/` directory — both `local/` and `devnet/` subdirectories\n2. What the coinflip E2E tests look like (pattern to follow)\n3. What `localnet-bootstrap.sh` does and where it is\n4. How E2E tests are configured (playwright config, package.json scripts for e2e)\n5. What test utilities/helpers exist for E2E\n\nBe very thorough - read all relevant files in full. Look at:\n- `sources/rng-utopia/e2e/` (all subdirectories)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh` or similar\n- `sources/rng-utopia/playwright.config.ts` or similar e2e config\n- `sources/rng-utopia/package.json` for e2e scripts\n- Any existing coinflip e2e tests","agentId":"a582ec9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the E2E test structure. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## E2E Test Structure Exploration - Complete Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the rng-utopia E2E test infrastructure. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\nsources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/\n├── fixtures.ts                           (base Playwright fixture - visual regression)\n├── local/                                (local validator E2E tests)\n│   ├── 00-smoke.spec.ts\n│   ├── 01-error-flow.spec.ts\n│   ├── 02-cancel-flow.spec.ts\n│   ├── 03-lifecycle.spec.ts\n│   ├── fixtures.ts                       (dual-player fixture with keypair injection)\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── wallets.ts                    (deterministic keypairs PLAYER_A/B)\n│       ├── localnet-setup.ts             (program config init)\n│       ├── on-chain.ts                   (PDA helpers, assertions)\n│       └── page-objects.ts               (UI selectors, action helpers)\n├── devnet/                               (devnet E2E tests with real VRF)\n│   ├── fixtures.ts                       (same dual-player pattern)\n│   ├── smoke.spec.ts\n│   ├── lifecycle.spec.ts\n│   └── helpers/\n│       ├── env.ts                        (env var validation)\n│       └── vrf-polling.ts                (robust VRF fulfillment polling)\n├── real/\n│   └── startup.spec.ts\n├── visual/                               (visual regression tests)\n│   ├── routes.spec.ts\n│   └── states.spec.ts\n└── __snapshots__/                        (PNG baselines for visual tests)\n```\n\n### 2. What Exists\n\n#### **Local E2E Tests** (`local/`)\n- **00-smoke.spec.ts**: Minimal test - app loads, wallet icon visible, no console errors\n- **01-error-flow.spec.ts**: Three tests running serially\n  - Insufficient balance error on match creation\n  - Join unavailable (cancelled) match error\n  - Settle already-claimed match error\n- **02-cancel-flow.spec.ts**: Single test - create → cancel → verify refund → recreate\n- **03-lifecycle.spec.ts**: Full game cycle - create → join → real VRF resolve (pre-mocked) → claim → verify profiles\n- **Dual-player fixtures**: Two isolated browser contexts (`playerAPage`, `playerBPage`) with deterministic keypairs injected\n\n#### **Devnet E2E Tests** (`devnet/`)\n- **smoke.spec.ts**: Three smoke tests\n  1. Verify devnet deployments (RPC health, programs deployed, VRF initialized)\n  2. App loads against devnet\n  3. Wallet connects with test keypair\n- **lifecycle.spec.ts**: Full devnet lifecycle with real VRF fulfillment\n  - Dual strategy: on-chain polling (exponential backoff) + UI wait in parallel\n  - Real Orao VRF callback triggers phase transition (locked → resolved)\n  - Handles non-deterministic outcome (either player can win)\n  - Comprehensive logging for diagnostics\n\n#### **Visual Regression Tests** (`visual/`)\n- **routes.spec.ts**: 12 route baseline snapshots (home, coinflip, crash, profile, 404, etc.)\n- **states.spec.ts**: Connected/disconnected states for home and coinflip pages\n- Uses deterministic `stablePage` fixture that:\n  - Seeds Math.random() with seed 42 (Mulberry32 PRNG)\n  - Freezes Date.now() to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n  - Disables all CSS/SVG animations\n  - Waits for fonts.ready and network idle\n  - Detects console errors and fails test if any found\n\n#### **Real Wallet Tests** (`real/`)\n- **startup.spec.ts**: Placeholder test file (minimal content)\n\n---\n\n### 3. Coinflip E2E Test Pattern (Local)\n\nThe **local coinflip tests follow a clear progression**:\n\n**Test Flow (01-error-flow.spec.ts → 02-cancel-flow.spec.ts → 03-lifecycle.spec.ts):**\n\n```\nTest 1: Insufficient Balance\n├─ Fund Player A with 0.001 SOL (below iron tier requirement of 0.005)\n├─ Navigate to coinflip → select iron tier + heads side\n├─ Click \"Create Game\" → error toast appears\n└─ Verify no match created on-chain (PDA closed)\n\nTest 2: Cancel Flow\n├─ Fund Player A with 10 SOL\n├─ Create match → verify balance decreases\n├─ Cancel match → lobby clears, refund received\n├─ Verify match PDA closed\n└─ Recreate immediately → new match with different side\n\nTest 3: Full Lifecycle (Dual-player)\n├─ Player A creates match (iron, heads)\n├─ Player B sees match in lobby → joins\n├─ Both wait for VRF (pre-fulfilled: HEADS → A wins)\n├─ A claims payout (match PDA closes)\n└─ Verify on-chain: treasury fee, player profiles (games/wins/wagered/won)\n```\n\n**Key Selectors & Actions** (`page-objects.ts`):\n- Tier selector: `.rng-tier-btn:has(.rng-tier-gem--{tier})`\n- Side buttons: `.coinflip-side-btn--{heads|tails}`\n- Match cards: `.coinflip-match-card` (own, claimable, joinable)\n- Active match states: `.coinflip-active-match__{waiting|playing}`\n- Results: `.coinflip-active-match__title--{won|lost}`\n- Error toasts: `.coinflip-error-toast`\n\n---\n\n### 4. localnet-bootstrap.sh Deep Dive\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n\n**What it does:**\n\n1. **Preflight checks**: Ensures `.so` files, keypairs exist\n2. **Kills old validator**: Checks `.localnet.pid`, kills on port 8899 if stray\n3. **Cleans ledger**: Removes `.localnet-ledger/` for fresh state\n4. **Starts validator** with:\n   - Two programs preloaded at genesis:\n     - Coinflip program (`BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx`)\n     - Platform program (`85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA`)\n   - Three Orao mock accounts pre-loaded (deterministic for tests):\n     - `5ER1oENnV4srxYdAynUfRzWeQCPQaqMiAp4VqyMbSqnK` (orao-network-state)\n     - `S4ne8ejGPUwNMNsE8L7gtjbTaBLBfVGdWNH6VQrL58a` (orao-random-player-a)\n     - `Ecs89dz8NsNoSxyUtp54G2HPbmvJr8qZnxnWUqiLT92r` (orao-treasury)\n5. **Waits for RPC**: Polls `getHealth` at `http://127.0.0.1:8899` up to 30s\n6. **Writes PID**: Saves to `.localnet.pid` for teardown\n\n**Important notes:**\n- Solana 3.x requires `io_uring`; Docker needs `--security-opt=seccomp=unconfined`\n- Script doesn't fail on io_uring check — lets validator fail naturally\n- All mock accounts in `scripts/localnet-accounts/` (JSON format for pre-initialization)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Playwright Configuration\n\n**Four configs in `apps/platform/`:**\n\n| Config | Port | Env Mode | Purpose |\n|--------|------|----------|---------|\n| `playwright.config.ts` | 3000 | MOCK | Visual regression tests (`visual/**`) |\n| `playwright.local.config.ts` | 3002 | TEST_WALLET=true, localnet RPC | Local E2E (`local/**`) |\n| `playwright.devnet.config.ts` | 3003 | TEST_WALLET=true, devnet RPC | Devnet E2E (`devnet/**`) |\n| `playwright.real.config.ts` | 3001 | Real wallet, devnet RPC | Real mode tests (`real/**`) |\n\n**Common Settings:**\n- Workers: 1 (serial execution for E2E)\n- Timeout: 60s–120s (120s for devnet due to VRF latency)\n- Trace: `retain-on-failure` for E2E, `off` for visual\n- Screenshot: off (unless visual tests use `toHaveScreenshot`)\n\n**Test-specific env vars in webServer:**\n```typescript\n// Local\nVITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"\nVITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\"\nVITE_RPC_URL: \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK: \"localnet\"\n\n// Devnet\nVITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"\nVITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\"\n// VITE_RPC_URL inherited from process env (validated in devnet/helpers/env.ts)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Package.json E2E Scripts\n\n```json\n{\n  \"test:visual\": \"playwright test\",\n  \"test:visual:update\": \"playwright test --update-snapshots\",\n  \"test:real\": \"playwright test --config playwright.real.config.ts\",\n  \"test:e2e:local\": \"playwright test --config playwright.local.config.ts\",\n  \"test:e2e\": \"bash scripts/run-e2e-local.sh\",\n  \"test:e2e:devnet\": \"bash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh\"\n}\n```\n\n**Three execution modes:**\n1. **Direct Playwright**: `npm run test:e2e:local` (assumes validator already running)\n2. **Full pipeline (local)**: `npm run test:e2e` (bootstrap → test → teardown)\n3. **Devnet**: `npm run test:e2e:devnet` (no bootstrap; requires env vars)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Test Utilities & Helpers\n\n#### **wallets.ts** (Deterministic)\n```typescript\nPLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(0xaa * 32 bytes)\nPLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(0xbb * 32 bytes)\nLOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\"\n\nfundWallet(connection, to, solAmount = 10)\nfundTestWallets(rpcUrl, solAmount) → returns both keypairs + connection\n```\n\n#### **localnet-setup.ts** (Initialization)\n```typescript\nADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(0xdd * 32 bytes)\nTREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(0xcc * 32 bytes)\n\ninitializeLocalnet()\n  └─ Funds admin & treasury (2 SOL each)\n  └─ Initializes coinflip config PDA\n  └─ Initializes platform config PDA\n  └─ Idempotent (checks if already exists)\n\nensurePlayerProfiles()\n  └─ Creates player profile PDAs for test wallets\n  └─ Separated from initializeLocalnet() to preserve test balances\n```\n\n#### **on-chain.ts** (RPC Helpers)\n```typescript\n// PDA derivation\ngetMatchPda(creator) → [PublicKey, bump]\ngetPlayerProfilePda(wallet) → [PublicKey, bump]\n\n// Fetching\nfetchMatch(connection, pda) → MatchAccount | null\nfetchPlayerProfile(connection, pda) → PlayerProfileAccount | null\n\n// Assertions\nassertMatchCreated(connection, creator, tier, side)\nassertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)\nassertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)\nassertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)\nassertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)\n\n// Snapshots\nsnapshotBalance(connection, address)\nsnapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)\n\n// Fee calculation\ncalculateExpectedFee(entryAmount)\n  └─ Returns { pool, fee: floor(pool * 300 bps / 10000), payout }\n```\n\n#### **page-objects.ts** (UI Actions)\n```typescript\n// Navigation\nnavigateToCoinflip(page)\n\n// Creation flow\nselectTier(page, tier: \"iron\" | \"bronze\" | ... | \"diamond\")\nselectSide(page, side: \"heads\" | \"tails\")\ncreateMatch(page, tier, side)\n\n// Joining\njoinMatch(page, matchIndex = 0)\nwaitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout)\n\n// Settlement\nclaimOrSettle(page)      // Click claim/settle button\nbackToLobby(page)        // Return after claim\n\n// Waits & assertions\nwaitForResult(page, timeout) → \"won\" | \"lost\"\nwaitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout)\nassertErrorToast(page, messageSubstring, timeout)\nassertLobbyEmpty(page, timeout)\n\n// Diagnostics\ntrackConsoleErrors(page) → { errors, assertClean() }\ngetSolBalance(page, walletAddress) → number\nwaitForText(page, text, timeout)\n```\n\n#### **env.ts** (Devnet Validation)\n```typescript\nvalidateDevnetEnv() → DevnetConfig\n  └─ Validates VITE_RPC_URL, VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\n  └─ Throws with consolidated errors if any missing/invalid\n\nverifyDevnetDeployments(config)\n  └─ RPC health check\n  └─ Programs deployed & executable\n  └─ Orao VRF network state PDA exists\n```\n\n#### **vrf-polling.ts** (Devnet VRF Detection)\n```typescript\npollVrfFulfillment(connection, creator, timeoutMs)\n  └─ Polls match PDA phase: locked → resolved\n  └─ Exponential backoff: start 2s, max 10s\n  └─ Logs timing budget at each attempt\n  └─ Returns { match, matchPda, phase, elapsedMs, attempts }\n  └─ Throws VrfTimeoutError with signatures on failure\n\ncollectMatchSignatures(connection, matchPda, limit = 10)\nlogRecentSignatures(connection, address, label, limit = 5)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Test Fixture Architecture\n\n#### **Base Fixture** (`fixtures.ts` - root)\n```typescript\nstablePage: Page\n  ├─ Seeds Math.random (Mulberry32, seed 42)\n  ├─ Seeds crypto.getRandomValues\n  ├─ Freezes Date.now to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n  ├─ Injects CSS disabling animations/transitions\n  ├─ Pauses SVG SMIL animations\n  ├─ Waits for fonts.ready + network idle after every navigation\n  └─ Collects console errors, fails test if any found\n```\n\n#### **Local Fixture** (`local/fixtures.ts`)\n```typescript\nDualPlayerFixtures {\n  playerAContext, playerAPage, playerAKeypair\n  playerBContext, playerBPage, playerBKeypair\n  connection: Connection(LOCAL_RPC_URL)\n}\n```\nEach context injects seed via `addInitScript`, allowing `TestWalletProvider` to reconstruct keypair.\n\n#### **Devnet Fixture** (`devnet/fixtures.ts`)\n```typescript\nDevnetDualPlayerFixtures {\n  devnetConfig: DevnetConfig (validates env)\n  playerAContext, playerAPage, playerAKeypair\n  playerBContext, playerBPage, playerBKeypair\n  connection: Connection(devnetConfig.rpcUrl)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Execution Flow Diagram\n\n```\nrun-e2e-local.sh\n├─ localnet-bootstrap.sh\n│  ├─ Kill old validator\n│  ├─ Clean ledger\n│  ├─ Start solana-test-validator with programs + mock accounts\n│  └─ Wait for RPC ready\n├─ playwright test --config playwright.local.config.ts\n│  ├─ Start Vite dev server (port 3002, TEST_WALLET=true)\n│  ├─ Run e2e/local/**/*.spec.ts\n│  │  ├─ beforeAll: fundTestWallets(), initializeLocalnet(), ensurePlayerProfiles()\n│  │  ├─ Each test gets playerAPage, playerBPage fixtures\n│  │  └─ Serial execution (fullyParallel: false)\n│  └─ Report results\n└─ localnet-teardown.sh\n   ├─ Kill validator by PID\n   ├─ Kill stray on port 8899\n   ├─ Remove .localnet-ledger\n   └─ Remove .localnet-validator.log (unless --keep-logs)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. Key Contract Points for New Tests\n\n**For Local Coinflip E2E (pattern to follow):**\n1. Use `test.describe.configure({ mode: \"serial\" })` for multi-test suites\n2. Fund test wallets in `beforeAll` with amounts matching test goals\n3. Call `initializeLocalnet()` before any on-chain assertions\n4. Derive PDAs using `getMatchPda()`, `getPlayerProfilePda()`\n5. Use page-objects for all UI interactions\n6. Track console errors with `po.trackConsoleErrors()`\n7. Assert on-chain state with `assert*()` helpers from `on-chain.ts`\n8. Snapshot balances & profiles before transactions, assert deltas after\n\n**For Devnet Tests:**\n1. Validate env in fixture setup (`devnetConfig` fixture)\n2. Fund wallets in `beforeAll` with airdrop (retries twice on failure)\n3. Use `pollVrfFulfillment()` for VRF wait (logs timing budget)\n4. Run UI wait in parallel with on-chain poll (whichever resolves first)\n5. Handle non-deterministic outcomes (either player can win on real VRF)\n6. Log transaction signatures for post-failure diagnostics\n\n---\n\n### 11. Summary of Files\n\n**Total Files:**\n- **Test specs**: 8 files (4 local, 2 devnet, 1 real, 1 visual baseline)\n- **Helpers**: 8 files (wallets, localnet-setup, on-chain, page-objects, env, vrf-polling, fixtures x2)\n- **Config**: 4 playwright configs + 3 shell scripts\n- **Snapshots**: Visual regression baselines in `__snapshots__/`\n\n**Key Absolute Paths:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/localnet-teardown.sh`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts`\n\nThis structure provides a robust, well-organized E2E test suite with clear separation between local deterministic tests (mock VRF), devnet real tests (real Orao VRF), and visual regression baselines."}],"totalDurationMs":120028,"totalTokens":79257,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_inp