{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JB5r26QMSzvyXD29PapBRZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018QXifUfXe5KVGL4ALLeHmQ","name":"Task","input":{"subagent_type":"Explore","description":"Explore VRF mock account creation","prompt":"I need to understand how mock Orao VRF randomness accounts are created for local E2E testing. Specifically:\n\n1. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/vrf_orao.rs` - how the VRF request is made (what seed is used)\n2. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/lordofrngs/src/instructions/start_spin.rs` - what seed is used for VRF request\n3. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs` - how coinflip creates VRF request (for comparison)\n4. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/lordofrngs/src/instructions/claim_payout.rs` - how randomness is read\n5. Check the Orao randomness account structure - how the PDA address for Orao randomness is derived. Look at `orao-solana-vrf` dependency or how the mock is set up in test files.\n\nKey question: For the local E2E test, the mock Orao randomness account at `S4ne8ejGPUwNMNsE8L7gtjbTaBLBfVGdWNH6VQrL58a` has pre-loaded data. How is this address derived? Is it a PDA based on the VRF seed? What seed does coinflip use vs lordofrngs?\n\nAlso check `sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts` to see how mock VRF accounts are set up in bankrun tests - specifically `setMockRandomness` and how the mock VRF randomness account address is derived."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":260,"cache_read_input_tokens":87349,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":260},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3430a832-47ac-41dd-bbc6-e4b8a98508e0","uuid":"138ad079-bd60-4afa