{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AQPvKbWHgJNyVSzUc9Gz5Y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Devnet E2E environment contract.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Validates that all required environment variables are present and well-formed\n     5→ * before any devnet test runs. Fails fast with clear error messages so CI\n     6→ * doesn't waste time on doomed runs.\n     7→ *\n     8→ * Required env vars:\n     9→ *   VITE_RPC_URL             — Devnet RPC endpoint (https URL)\n    10→ *   VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID — Deployed coinflip program address (base58)\n    11→ *   VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID — Deployed platform program address (base58)\n    12→ *\n    13→ * Optional (with defaults):\n    14→ *   VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK      — Cluster name (default: \"devnet\")\n    15→ */\n    16→\n    17→import { Connection, PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n    18→\n    19→// Orao VRF program ID (hardcoded — same address on all clusters)\n    20→const ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n    21→  \"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\",\n    22→);\n    23→\n    24→/** Validated devnet configuration. */\n    25→export interface DevnetConfig {\n    26→  rpcUrl: string;\n    27→  network: string;\n    28→  coinflipProgramId: PublicKey;\n    29→  platformProgramId: PublicKey;\n    30→  oraoVrfProgramId: PublicKey;\n    31→}\n    32→\n    33→/** Validate a base58 public key string. Throws if invalid. */\n    34→function parsePublicKey(value: string, label: string): PublicKey {\n    35→  try {\n    36→    return new PublicKey(value);\n    37→  } catch {\n    38→    throw new Error(\n    39→      `${label} is not a valid Solana address (base58): \"${value}\"`,\n    40→    );\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→\n    44→/** Validate a URL string. Throws if malformed. */\n    45→function parseUrl(value: string, label: string): string {\n    46→  try {\n    47→    const url = new URL(value);\n    48→    if (![\"http:\", \"https:\"].includes(url.protocol)) {\n    49→      throw new Error(\"not http(s)\");\n    50→    }\n    51→    return value;\n    52→  } catch {\n    53→    throw new Error(\n    54→      `${label} is not a valid HTTP(S) URL: \"${value}\"`,\n    55→    );\n    56→  }\n    57→}\n    58→\n    59→/**\n    60→ * Read and validate all required devnet env vars.\n    61→ * Throws with a consolidated error listing every missing/invalid variable.\n    62→ */\n    63→export function validateDevnetEnv(): DevnetConfig {\n    64→  const errors: string[] = [];\n    65→\n    66→  // --- Required ---\n    67→  const rpcUrl = process.env.VITE_RPC_URL;\n    68→  if (!rpcUrl) {\n    69→    errors.push(\"VITE_RPC_URL is required (devnet RPC endpoint)\");\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  const coinflipId = process.env.VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID;\n    73→  if (!coinflipId) {\n    74→    errors.push(\n    75→      \"VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID is required (deployed coinflip program address)\",\n    76→    );\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→  const platformId = process.env.VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID;\n    80→  if (!platformId) {\n    81→    errors.push(\n    82→      \"VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID is required (deployed platform program address)\",\n    83→    );\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  // Fail fast if any required var is missing\n    87→  if (errors.length > 0) {\n    88→    throw new Error(\n    89→      `Devnet E2E env validation failed:\\n  - ${errors.join(\"\\n  - \")}\\n\\n` +\n    90→        `Hint: copy .env.devnet to .env.local and update program IDs, ` +\n    91→        `or export the variables before running tests.`,\n    92→    );\n    93→  }\n    94→\n    95→  // --- Format validation ---\n    96→  const validatedUrl = parseUrl(rpcUrl!, \"VITE_RPC_URL\");\n    97→  const coinflipProgramId = parsePublicKey(\n    98→    coinflipId!,\n    99→    \"VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID\",\n   100→  );\n   101→  const platformProgramId = parsePublicKey(\n   102→    platformId!,\n   103→    \"VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID\",\n   104→  );\n   105→\n   106→  // --- Optional with default ---\n   107→  const network = process.env.VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK ?? \"devnet\";\n   108→\n   109→  return {\n   110→    rpcUrl: validatedUrl,\n   111→    network,\n   112→    coinflipProgramId,\n   113→    platformProgramId,\n   114→    oraoVrfProgramId: ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID,\n   115→  };\n   116→}\n   117→\n   118→/**\n   119→ * Verify that the devnet RPC is reachable and that required programs\n   120→ * are deployed. Call this once in globalSetup or the first test's beforeAll.\n   121→ */\n   122→export async function verifyDevnetDeployments(\n   123→  config: DevnetConfig,\n   124→): Promise<void> {\n   125→  const connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n   126→\n   127→  // 1. RPC health check\n   128→  try {\n   129→    await connection.getLatestBlockhash();\n   130→  } catch (err) {\n   131→    throw new Error(\n   132→      `Cannot reach devnet RPC at ${config.rpcUrl}: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : err}`,\n   133→    );\n   134→  }\n   135→\n   136→  // 2. Coinflip program deployed\n   137→  const coinflipAccount = await connection.getAccountInfo(\n   138→    config.coinflipProgramId,\n   139→  );\n   140→  if (!coinflipAccount || !coinflipAccount.executable) {\n   141→    throw new Error(\n   142→      `Coinflip program not found or not executable at ${config.coinflipProgramId.toBase58()}`,\n   143→    );\n   144→  }\n   145→\n   146→  // 3. Platform program deployed\n   147→  const platformAccount = await connection.getAccountInfo(\n   148→    config.platformProgramId,\n   149→  );\n   150→  if (!platformAccount || !platformAccount.executable) {\n   151→    throw new Error(\n   152→      `Platform program not found or not executable at ${config.platformProgramId.toBase58()}`,\n   153→    );\n   154→  }\n   155→\n   156→  // 4. Orao VRF program deployed\n   157→  const oraoAccount = await connection.getAccountInfo(\n   158→    config.oraoVrfProgramId,\n   159→  );\n   160→  if (!oraoAccount || !oraoAccount.executable) {\n   161→    throw new Error(\n   162→      `Orao VRF program not found or not executable at ${config.oraoVrfProgramId.toBase58()}`,\n   163→    );\n   164→  }\n   165→\n   166→  // 5. Orao VRF network state PDA exists (proves VRF is initialized)\n   167→  const [oraoNetworkState] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n   168→    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")],\n   169→    config.oraoVrfProgramId,\n   170→  );\n   171→  const networkState = await connection.getAccountInfo(oraoNetworkState);\n   172→  if (!networkState) {\n   173→    throw new Error(\n   174→      `Orao VRF network state PDA not found at ${oraoNetworkState.toBase58()} — ` +\n   175→        `VRF provider may not be initialized on this cluster`,\n   176→    );\n   177→  }\n   178→}\n   179→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018QXifUfXe5KVGL4ALLeHmQ","session_id":"3430a832-47ac-41dd-bbc6-e4b8a98508e0","uuid":"58106f22-3dba-4742-b5d9-39b37d1a0e1c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018QXifUfXe5KVGL4ALLeHmQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document for the user.\n\n## Analysis Complete: Mock Orao VRF Randomness Account Creation\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, here's how mock Orao VRF randomness accounts are created and used in local E2E testing:\n\n### Key Findings\n\n#### 1. **VRF Seed Generation (What Seed is Used)**\n\nBoth **Coinflip** and **LordOfRngs** use the **game round/match PDA key itself as the VRF seed**:\n\n**Coinflip** (`join_match.rs` line 78):\n```rust\nlet seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key().to_bytes();\n```\n\n**LordOfRngs** (`start_spin.rs` line 80):\n```rust\nlet seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.round.key().to_bytes();\n```\n\nThis is elegant — each match/round gets a **unique, deterministic seed** derived from its own PDA address.\n\n#### 2. **Orao Randomness Account PDA Derivation**\n\nThe Orao randomness account address is **derived using the Orao VRF program**:\n\n**From `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` lines 53-59:**\n```typescript\n/** Orao VRF randomness PDA derived from a 32-byte seed. */\nfunction getOraoRandomnessPda(seed: Uint8Array): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\"), seed],\n    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n```\n\n**Formula:**\n- **Seeds**: `[\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\", <32-byte game seed>]`\n- **Program**: `VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y` (Orao VRF program ID, hardcoded)\n\n**Example flow for Coinflip:**\n1. Match PDA created: `match_pda = PDA([\"match\", creator])` from Coinflip program\n2. When opponent calls `join_match()`, the seed is set to `match_pda.key().to_bytes()`\n3. The randomness account is derived: `randomness_pda = PDA([\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\", match_pda], orao_program_id)`\n4. The match stores `vrf_request_key = randomness_pda.key()` for later lookup\n\n#### 3. **Mock VRF Setup in Bankrun Tests**\n\nIn the local **bankrun** tests, mock Orao accounts are created as simple Keypairs:\n\n**From `solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts` lines 84-109:**\n```typescript\nasync function createTestContext(): Promise<TestContext> {\n  const treasury = Keypair.generate();\n  const player2 = Keypair.generate();\n  const mockRandomness = Keypair.generate();        // Generated at random!\n  const mockOraoProgram = Keypair.generate();\n  const mockOraoNetworkState = Keypair.generate();\n  const mockOraoTreasury = Keypair.generate();\n\n  const context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n    // ... funded accounts ...\n    // Mock randomness account — starts unfulfilled (32 zero bytes)\n    {\n      address: mockRandomness.publicKey,\n      info: {\n        lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n        data: RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED,  // 32 zero bytes\n        owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n        executable: false,\n      },\n    },\n  ]);\n```\n\n**Key difference**: The test uses a **randomly generated Keypair** (`mockRandomness.publicKey`) instead of deriving a PDA. This bypasses the real Orao VRF derivation.\n\n#### 4. **Randomness Fulfillment (Mock vs Real)**\n\nIn **mock-vrf feature mode**:\n- `request_orao_randomness()` is a no-op (line 81 in `vrf_orao.rs`)\n- `read_orao_randomness()` reads raw 32 bytes from the account (lines 96-105)\n- Tests manually fulfill randomness using `setMockRandomness()` (line 257 in test):\n\n```typescript\nfunction setMockRandomness(t: TestContext, data: Buffer) {\n  t.context.setAccount(t.mockRandomness.publicKey, {\n    lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n    data,  // New 32-byte randomness (first byte determines outcome)\n    owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n    executable: false,\n  });\n}\n```\n\nIn **real mode** (production):\n- `request_orao_randomness()` calls `orao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2()` (line 48)\n- `read_orao_randomness()` deserializes real Orao `RandomnessAccountData` (line 63)\n- Orao oracle fulfills the request asynchronously\n\n#### 5. **How to Verify: Production E2E on Devnet**\n\nFor devnet E2E tests, the code:\n1. Derives Orao randomness PDA correctly using `getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes())`\n2. Passes this **derived** PDA address to the on-chain instruction\n3. Relies on the **real Orao VRF program** to fulfill it\n\n**From `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` lines 166-177:**\n```typescript\n// Orao VRF network state PDA exists (proves VRF is initialized)\nconst [oraoNetworkState] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n  [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")],\n  config.oraoVrfProgramId,\n);\nconst networkState = await connection.getAccountInfo(oraoNetworkState);\nif (!networkState) {\n  throw new Error(\n    `Orao VRF network state PDA not found at ${oraoNetworkState.toBase58()} — ` +\n      `VRF provider may not be initialized on this cluster`,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Aspect | Bankrun Tests (Mock) | Production (Devnet/Mainnet) |\n|--------|---------------------|---------------------------|\n| **VRF Seed** | Match/Round PDA key | Match/Round PDA key |\n| **Randomness Account Derivation** | Random Keypair (test-specific) | PDA from `[\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\", seed]` + Orao program ID |\n| **VRF Request** | No-op (mock-vrf feature) | Real CPI to Orao program |\n| **Randomness Fulfillment** | Manual via `setMockRandomness()` | Orao oracle (async) |\n| **Account Data** | Raw 32 bytes (all zeros until set) | Orao `RandomnessAccountData` struct (64-byte randomness) |\n\n### File Locations\n\n- **VRF shared logic**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/vrf_orao.rs`\n- **Coinflip VRF request**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs` (line 78)\n- **LordOfRngs VRF request**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/lordofrngs/src/instructions/start_spin.rs` (line 80)\n- **Client PDA derivation**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` (lines 53-59)\n- **Bankrun test setup**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts` (lines 84-265)\n- **Devnet validation**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` (lines 166-177)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a4fa2f0 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 77968\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 111248</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3430a832-47ac-41dd-bbc6-e4b8a98508e0","uuid":"27561e47-b3cc-4f8c-841f-5b3408906dd0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how mock Orao VRF randomness accounts are created for local E2E testing. Specifically:\n\n1. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/vrf_orao.rs` - how the VRF request is made (what seed is used)\n2. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/lordofrngs/src/instructions/start_spin.rs` - what seed is used for VRF request\n3. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs` - how coinflip creates VRF request (for comparison)\n4. Read `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/lordofrngs/src/instructions/claim_payout.rs` - how randomness is read\n5. Check the Orao randomness account structure - how the PDA address for Orao randomness is derived. Look at `orao-solana-vrf` dependency or how the mock is set up in test files.\n\nKey question: For the local E2E test, the mock Orao randomness account at `S4ne8ejGPUwNMNsE8L7gtjbTaBLBfVGdWNH6VQrL58a` has pre-loaded data. How is this address derived? Is it a PDA based on the VRF seed? What seed does coinflip use vs lordofrngs?\n\nAlso check `sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts` to see how mock VRF accounts are set up in bankrun tests - specifically `setMockRandomness` and how the mock VRF randomness account address is derived.","agentId":"a4fa2f0","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a summary document for the user.\n\n## Analysis Complete: Mock Orao VRF Randomness Account Creation\n\nBased on my analysis of the codebase, here's how mock Orao VRF randomness accounts are created and used in local E2E testing:\n\n### Key Findings\n\n#### 1. **VRF Seed Generation (What Seed is Used)**\n\nBoth **Coinflip** and **LordOfRngs** use the **game round/match PDA key itself as the VRF seed**:\n\n**Coinflip** (`join_match.rs` line 78):\n```rust\nlet seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.key().to_bytes();\n```\n\n**LordOfRngs** (`start_spin.rs` line 80):\n```rust\nlet seed: [u8; 32] = ctx.accounts.round.key().to_bytes();\n```\n\nThis is elegant — each match/round gets a **unique, deterministic seed** derived from its own PDA address.\n\n#### 2. **Orao Randomness Account PDA Derivation**\n\nThe Orao randomness account address is **derived using the Orao VRF program**:\n\n**From `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` lines 53-59:**\n```typescript\n/** Orao VRF randomness PDA derived from a 32-byte seed. */\nfunction getOraoRandomnessPda(seed: Uint8Array): PublicKey {\n  const [pda] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n    [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\"), seed],\n    ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID\n  );\n  return pda;\n}\n```\n\n**Formula:**\n- **Seeds**: `[\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\", <32-byte game seed>]`\n- **Program**: `VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y` (Orao VRF program ID, hardcoded)\n\n**Example flow for Coinflip:**\n1. Match PDA created: `match_pda = PDA([\"match\", creator])` from Coinflip program\n2. When opponent calls `join_match()`, the seed is set to `match_pda.key().to_bytes()`\n3. The randomness account is derived: `randomness_pda = PDA([\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\", match_pda], orao_program_id)`\n4. The match stores `vrf_request_key = randomness_pda.key()` for later lookup\n\n#### 3. **Mock VRF Setup in Bankrun Tests**\n\nIn the local **bankrun** tests, mock Orao accounts are created as simple Keypairs:\n\n**From `solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts` lines 84-109:**\n```typescript\nasync function createTestContext(): Promise<TestContext> {\n  const treasury = Keypair.generate();\n  const player2 = Keypair.generate();\n  const mockRandomness = Keypair.generate();        // Generated at random!\n  const mockOraoProgram = Keypair.generate();\n  const mockOraoNetworkState = Keypair.generate();\n  const mockOraoTreasury = Keypair.generate();\n\n  const context = await startAnchor(\"./\", [], [\n    // ... funded accounts ...\n    // Mock randomness account — starts unfulfilled (32 zero bytes)\n    {\n      address: mockRandomness.publicKey,\n      info: {\n        lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n        data: RANDOMNESS_UNFULFILLED,  // 32 zero bytes\n        owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n        executable: false,\n      },\n    },\n  ]);\n```\n\n**Key difference**: The test uses a **randomly generated Keypair** (`mockRandomness.publicKey`) instead of deriving a PDA. This bypasses the real Orao VRF derivation.\n\n#### 4. **Randomness Fulfillment (Mock vs Real)**\n\nIn **mock-vrf feature mode**:\n- `request_orao_randomness()` is a no-op (line 81 in `vrf_orao.rs`)\n- `read_orao_randomness()` reads raw 32 bytes from the account (lines 96-105)\n- Tests manually fulfill randomness using `setMockRandomness()` (line 257 in test):\n\n```typescript\nfunction setMockRandomness(t: TestContext, data: Buffer) {\n  t.context.setAccount(t.mockRandomness.publicKey, {\n    lamports: LAMPORTS_PER_SOL,\n    data,  // New 32-byte randomness (first byte determines outcome)\n    owner: SystemProgram.programId,\n    executable: false,\n  });\n}\n```\n\nIn **real mode** (production):\n- `request_orao_randomness()` calls `orao_solana_vrf::cpi::request_v2()` (line 48)\n- `read_orao_randomness()` deserializes real Orao `RandomnessAccountData` (line 63)\n- Orao oracle fulfills the request asynchronously\n\n#### 5. **How to Verify: Production E2E on Devnet**\n\nFor devnet E2E tests, the code:\n1. Derives Orao randomness PDA correctly using `getOraoRandomnessPda(matchPda.toBytes())`\n2. Passes this **derived** PDA address to the on-chain instruction\n3. Relies on the **real Orao VRF program** to fulfill it\n\n**From `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` lines 166-177:**\n```typescript\n// Orao VRF network state PDA exists (proves VRF is initialized)\nconst [oraoNetworkState] = PublicKey.findProgramAddressSync(\n  [Buffer.from(\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\")],\n  config.oraoVrfProgramId,\n);\nconst networkState = await connection.getAccountInfo(oraoNetworkState);\nif (!networkState) {\n  throw new Error(\n    `Orao VRF network state PDA not found at ${oraoNetworkState.toBase58()} — ` +\n      `VRF provider may not be initialized on this cluster`,\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Aspect | Bankrun Tests (Mock) | Production (Devnet/Mainnet) |\n|--------|---------------------|---------------------------|\n| **VRF Seed** | Match/Round PDA key | Match/Round PDA key |\n| **Randomness Account Derivation** | Random Keypair (test-specific) | PDA from `[\"orao-vrf-randomness-request\", seed]` + Orao program ID |\n| **VRF Request** | No-op (mock-vrf feature) | Real CPI to Orao program |\n| **Randomness Fulfillment** | Manual via `setMockRandomness()` | Orao oracle (async) |\n| **Account Data** | Raw 32 bytes (all zeros until set) | Orao `RandomnessAccountData` struct (64-byte randomness) |\n\n### File Locations\n\n- **VRF shared logic**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/src/vrf_orao.rs`\n- **Coinflip VRF request**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/join_match.rs` (line 78)\n- **LordOfRngs VRF request**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/lordofrngs/src/instructions/start_spin.rs` (line 80)\n- **Client PDA derivation**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` (lines 53-59)\n- **Bankrun test setup**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/lordofrngs.ts` (lines 84-265)\n- **Devnet validation**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` (lines 166-177)"}],"totalDurationMs":111248,"totalTokens":77968,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2498,"cache_read_input_tokens":73345,"output_tokens":2120,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2498,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Lrb1HDZqoPxuQTaH7cFsup","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full picture. For local E2E tests, the key challenge is that Lord of RNGs uses the **round PDA key** as the VRF seed, and the Orao randomness account is a PDA derived from that seed. Unlike coinflip (where the match PDA is deterministic from `[\"match\", creator]`), Lord of RNGs round PDAs use `[\"jackpot_round\", tier, round_number]` — which IS deterministic.\n\nLet me understand the flow better by checking how the coinflip local E2E handles VRF — the mock randomness account `S4ne8ejGPUwNMNsE8L7gtjbTaBLBfVGdWNH6VQrL58a` must be pre-loaded with fulfilled data at the right address."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2743,"cache_read_input_tokens":87609,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2743},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3430a832-47ac-41dd-bbc6-e4b8a98508e0","uuid":"47369269-6608-4700-9a83-d8e541bd2cf3"}
